[[Category:Lines of latitude|n75]]
[[Category:Geography of the Arctic]]

'''Absyrtides''' or '''Apsyrtides''' or '''Apsirtides''' ({{lang-grc|Ἀψυρτίδες}}) was a collective name of two islands off the coast of [[Illyricum (Roman province)|Illyricum]] &ndash; [[Cres]] and [[Lošinj]], which were almost attached. The name recalls [[Absyrtus]], who according to one tradition, was slain here by his sister [[Medea]] and by [[Jason]]. [[Ptolemy]] mentions only one island, ''Apsorrus'' (Ἄψορρος), on which he places two towns [[Cres (town)|Crepsa]] (Κρέψα) (the modern [[Cres (town)|Cres]]) and [[Osor, Croatia|Apsorrus]] (the modern [[Osor, Croatia|Osor]], now all in [[Croatia]]).
==References== *[[Stephanus of Byzantium|Steph. Byz.]] ''s.v.'' *[[Pomponius Mela|Mel.]] 2.7. *[[Pliny the Elder|Plin.]] [[Natural History (Pliny)|N. H.]] 3.26. *[[Ptolemy|Ptol.]] [[Geography (Ptolemy)|Geog.]] 2.16.13. *{{DGRG|title=Absyrtides}}
