{{Infobox Waterfall | name = Duduma Waterfall | native_name = {{lang|or|ଡୁଡୁମା ଜଳପ୍ରପାତ}} | image = | caption = | map = Orissa | map_caption = Waterfall place in [[Odisha]] | coordinates = {{coord|18|31|6.68|N|82|27|12.83|E|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Koraput District]], [[Odisha]], [[India]] | elevation = | type = | height = 157 meter | height_longest = | average_width = | number_drops = 1 | average_flow = | watercourse = }}
The '''Duduma Waterfall''', {{Convert|175|m|ft}} high,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://koraput.nic.in/New/Tourist/duduma.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-03-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415055523/http://koraput.nic.in/New/Tourist/duduma.htm |archivedate=2012-04-15 |df= }}</ref> is formed by the [[Machkund]] river in [[Odisha]] & [[Andhra Pradesh]] states of [[India]].<ref name="siliconindia">{{cite web|url=http://travel.siliconindia.com/travel-article/Duduma-Waterfall-Koraput-aid-2305.html|title=Duduma Waterfall|date= |website=siliconindia.com|access-date=27 November 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.whereincity.com/photo-gallery/waterfalls/duduma-waterfall-658.htm whereincity.com: Duduma Waterfall - Koraput]</ref> [[File:Duduma Falls.jpg|thumb|Duduma Falls]] Duduma is about 92&nbsp;km from [[Koraput]] and about 177&nbsp;km from Visakhapatnam. It forms a part of the boundary between Andhra Pradesh and Odisha.
Duduma Waterfalls is one of the highest waterfalls in India. Its waters support a large [[Hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] project called Machkund Hydro Electric Power Project located at 'Onukudelli'. Machkund is an important place for [[pilgrimage]]. The name Machkund derived from a pilgrimage point called 'Matsya Kunda'near the township of Paderu in Andhra Pradesh. A beautiful township called 'Onukudelli' has grown around this lovely place. The aboriginal tribe of 'Bondas' live near this waterfalls. It has two sub-waterfalls one on the Odisha side and the other on the Andhra Pradesh side. The waterfalls lie in picturesque surroundings. It is one of the best tourist spots in Southern India.
==See also== *[[List of waterfalls in India]] *[[List of waterfalls in India by height]]
