{{Expand French|Pierre Duval|date=January 2012}}
'''Pierre Duval''' (1618–1683) was a [[France|French]] geographer.

Pierre Duval was born in [[Abbeville]]. He was the nephew and pupil of the geographer [[Nicolas Sanson]]. Encouraged by [[Louis XIV of France|Louis XIV]] to move to [[Paris]], he later became [[Geographe Ordinaire du Roy]].<ref name="Betz2007">{{cite book|author=Richard L. Betz|title=The mapping of Africa: a cartobibliography of printed maps of the African continent to 1700|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c8cYAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=13 May 2013|year=2007|publisher=Hes & de Graaf|isbn=978-90-6194-489-8|page=319}}</ref>

