{{Infobox Hindu temple | name = Somsar Sri Ramakrishna Seva Mandir <!-- Please do not add any Indic script in this infobox, per WP:INDICSCRIPT policy. --> | image = | alt = | caption = Somsar Sri Ramakrishna Seva Mandir | map_type = India West Bengal | map_caption = Location in West Bengal | other_names = Somsar Sri Ramakrishna | country = [[India]] | state = [[West Bengal]] | district = [[Bankura]] | location = [[Somsar]] | coordinates = {{coord|23|13|26|N|87|38|20|E|type:landmark_region:IN-WB|display=inline,title}}
| architecture = Fusion of [[Hindu]] and [[Christian]] | temple_quantity = 1 | inscriptions = none | creator = [[Ramakrishna Mission]] | website = {{url|http://www.somsar.org/}} }}
'''Somsar Sri Ramakrishna Seva Mandir''' is a temple erected to commemorate the birthplace and the humanitarian activities spearheaded by Srimat Swami Bhuteshanandaji, the 12th President of Belur Math. Srimat Swami Bhuteshanandaji was born in [[Somsar]] Village and when he grew older he started his spiritual journey eventually culminated in becoming a monk and serving the needs of the poor via [[Ramakrishna Math and Mission]] and its numerable religious and charitable activities.
The temple was officially inaugurated in 18 December 2015. It has a spacious prayer hall that can accommodate a minimum 200 devotees at a time. As of now, Somsar Sri Ramakrishna Seva Mandir is involved in various religious, education and social work activities.
[[Category:Hindu temples in India]]
{{building-stub}}

{{Infobox lake |name = Sovetskaya Lake |image = Sovetskaya lake modis 2004 lrg.jpg |caption = A satellite greyscale image of 90° East Lake and Sovetskaya Lake |image_bathymetry = |caption_bathymetry = |coords = {{coord|77|58|S|89|16|E|source:frwiki_scale:1000000_region:AQ|display=title,inline}} |type = [[subglacial lake|subglacial]] |inflow = |outflow = |catchment = |location = [[Antarctica]] |basin_countries = (Antarctica) |length = |width = |area = {{convert|1,600|km2|abbr=on}} |depth = |max-depth = |volume = |residence_time = |shore = |elevation = |islands = |cities = }} '''Sovetskaya Lake''' is a liquid [[subglacial lake]] found buried under the [[Antarctic]] ice sheet, {{convert|2|km|ft}} below [[Sovetskaya (Antarctic Research Station)|Sovetskaya Research Station]]. It covers about {{convert|1600|km2|mi2}}.<ref>{{cite web | last = Kostel | first = Ken | title = Two New Lakes Found Beneath Antarctic Ice Sheet | publisher = Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory |date=January 2006 | url = http://www.ldeo.columbia.edu/news/2006/01_25_06.htm | accessdate = 2007-12-03 }}</ref>
